This is a standard DE map with 2 bombsites and 64 spawn points. Each bombsite has at least 3 points of entry. This map was meticulously rebuilt from the ground-up to be very close to the original de_survivor by 3D Mike. Thorough beta testing shows that framerates are well within the acceptable range for serious play, but you can expect this map to be as taxing as de_nuke or de_inferno. This map was created for and is in rotation at the [DoP] High Times servers.

Note that while this map does come with a .NAV file, it is not optimized. Bots are over-rated.

STORY:
A high priority informant has been shot down by enemy forces in a remote mountainous area. A local private security force has been contracted by the US to be America's first response in bringing the plane crash survivor into custody for interogation. The survivor has locked himself in the cockpit of the plane wreckage.

Counter-Terrorist objective is to secure the immobilized target until the 2nd American team arrives.

Terrorist objective is to execute the target or otherwise prevent his extraction by US forces.

ATTENTION !!

This version is easier to play, less detailed, has more fps and no hdr (not used in pcws) and some tweaks to make it play better in 5on5 matches. Anyway it can be played on public ones. I'll release an HDR version once It has been tested enough.

Changes in BETA2:
-Color correction is now static and less red (so the filesize is lower).
-Clip added to the windows in the hangar and other spots.
-Reduced the number of props in the map (some people told me it was hard to play because it was too detailed).
-Blocked some spots and simplified few details to make it easier to play (there were to many spots to hide and people didn't like it in pcws).
-Changed a bit the layout so now T reach 1 to 3sec later bombsite A.
-Slightly fps improve due to the amount of props and details deleted.
-Dramatic fps improve in T's base and grave ramp.
-Ambient light is now a bit more light.
-Some cubemaps have been reduced and two deleted so the filesize is lower now.
-There is only 1 Color correction file so filesize will be like 1mb lower for this.
-Radar is now compressed so it weights 1/3 (~3mb now,  ~10mb before).
-Sound effects are now generic (people didn't like the eco and sound distortion in some areas so now there is no distorsion).
-Many prop distances have been reduced and faded to improve fps on lowend PC's.
-Improved spawn points to make it easier or harder to rush in some rounds and added 8 spawn points more (40 now)

Notes:
-Best seen with Color correction + HDR + gamma 2.2 (remember to add sv_allow_color_correction 1)
-Beta test. Feedback is appreciated!
-Meant to be played for 5on5 games but has up to 40 spawn points
-Do not decompile without authorization. PM on FPSBANANA, INTERLOPERS, 
MAPCORE or HL2SPAIN if you want to know how has something been done or
just for feedback. acc: Deh0lise / Deh0

Install notes:
Extract to cstrike/maps/

A terrorist guerrilla unit has infiltrated the ancient sunken temple, looking for its reported treasures. The terrorists raided the temple grounds killing civilian researchers.  They then began looking for the treasure they thought was buried somewhere on the site.

However, the terrorists would rather blow up the temples than let any treasure fall into the hands of the enemy! The counter-terrorists must protect the two targets from the suicidal terrorists. 

This is the second version of Sunken Temple.  This version gets rid of the original Bombsite A and combines it into the CT spawn.  The result is that the map is smaller and easier to play on with fewer players. The running time between the two bombsites is significantly shorter compared to the original map.

The Original map can be found here: [http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/154320](http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/154320 "http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/154320")

Description
==================
This is my first map I created for Counter-Strike: Source. Although I do not play it myself I decided to try out making a bigger map than the previous testmaps for Half-Life 2. The setting is an abandoned outlying district of an American city after it has been evacuated due to heavy terrorism. Deserted buildings, destroyed cars and much trash on the streets show the results of brutal devastation.

Gameplay
==================
As the screenshots show the map is very open so playing with sniper rifles could be easy. It is not too complex so players should be able to memorize the map easily.

Performance
==================
I have put a lot of time into optimizing the map, though on some low-end computers or computers with a high resolution monitor the framerate might drop when switching on the flashlight at certain points. However, the map is well-lighted so the flashlight should not be necessary for playing.

Installation
==================
Extract the bsp-file from the zip folder into the directory

**c:\programs\Steam\steamapps\[username]\counter-strike\source\cstrike\maps**

(default Steam directory)

Feedback
==================
**Any feedback will be appreciated!** Tell me what you think about the layout and the gameplay, should it be more complex or whatsoever so I will make my maps better next time.

Looks big, but actually small! This is the tiniest bomb/defuse map possible for Source within reason. The bomb targets and the spawns are positioned on the four corners of a small, imaginary sqaure, such that the T and CT spawns are next door to each other. This map plays FAST as it only takes seconds to get to the bomb targets or the other team.

De_subside

3 subway stations, 2 teams, 2 trains.

The teams start at opposite ends of the map. There are three subway stations, and the middle one is the bomb target. And yes, you can ride the trains. 

I've always wanted a map like this, but never found one. So I built one myself. Everything works extremely well, never thought it would turn out this good. It's not that big, and the bombtarget is in the middle, which should keep round times down. The trains move back and forth along the whole map. 


So download NOW! This is an awesome map every server should host!

A while ago I had the idea to create a map with the ability to recognize the player's actions, and change accordingly. This resulted in de_struction, my prefix for Bomb/Defusal maps, with fake DMM.

Basically, this map is an office ripoff with walls that break apart. It supports up to 10 players at any time, and is fully-functioning, with buyzones and a bombsite.

I'm still looking to improve it, and make more maps like it. (Although, a bit more inspired & complete.)

To be clear, this map is nowhere near complete, nor do I intend for it to be a competitive map.

Thanks to 3kliksphilip for the idea.

Also, if you can help me out in any way/shape/form then please add me on steam or comment below. (Username is same as on GB)

De_stronghold

A team of terrorists are infiltrating an underground bunker, which houses important military information and supplies. 

As terrorists your objective is to destroy the generators, which will cut off the facility's power supply. Alternatively, blow up the data servers and land a crippling blow on the military's intelligence operations. 

As counter-terrorists your objective is to stop the terrorists accomplishing their objective at all costs.
